basic preferences(I'm happy to provide more specifics here if necessary)\r\n\t\t\r\nIt looks like we're taking the wrong action based on this check at RecommenderJob.java:122\r\n\r\nPath usersFile = hasOption(\"usersFile\") ? inputFile : new Path(getOption(\"usersFile\"));\r\n\r\nIf the usersFile option has been specified, it seems like we should be using that, rather than the inputFile, and vice versa.\r\n\r\nI have attached attached a patch, runnable from trunk that swaps the action on line 122.  This appears to fix the issue.","customfield_10010":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_12312026":null,"customfield_12312023":null,"customfield_12312024":null,"customfield_12312340":null,"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"customfield_12312022":null,"customfield_12312341":null,"customfield_12312220":null,"customfield_12310921":null,"customfield_12310920":"22385","summary":"org.apache.mahout.cf.taste.hadoop.pseudo.RecommenderJob throws IllegalArgumentException when no usersFile is supplied","creator":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=dcartoon","name":"dcartoon","emailAddress":"dcartoon at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Dan Cartoon","active":true},"subtasks":[],"customfield_12310291":null,"reporter":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=dcartoon","name":"dcartoon","emailAddress":"dcartoon at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.